ht, which were won by Ericco.  Note that Need Before Greed was clearly posted, and announced during the rolling.  Less than a day later, Ericco posted that he was selling the Gauntlets (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm2.showMessage?topicID=3066.topic">link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->).  Backlash from the community was immediate and fierce.  Another thread was spawned in the Soapbox forum (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessage?topicID=1015.topic">link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->).<br><br>After monitoring the threads for a couple days and unsuccessfully trying to contact Ericco and Bobmata (his guild leader) in game, I finally posted my response in Ericco's Market Square thread.  Essentially, until we come up with a way for him to redeem himself he is banned from my raids.<br><br>So, the question I have for all of you reading this is the following:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  What does Ericco need to do in order to be redeemed in the open raid community?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Ideas I have so far:<br><br>1) Return the Gauntlets for redistribution (already sold so not very likely)<br>2) Hand over all proceeds for use to fund future raids.<br>3) Hand over twice all proceeds for use to fund future raids (or some other multiple)<br>4) Attend 1-5 open raids without rolling on any loot.<br>5) Attend open raids until he wins 1 or more items, but doesn't get to keep the item(s).<br><br>In a day or two I will consolidate a list of ideas and post them as a poll to get public opinion.<br><br>------------------------------------------------------------<br>Some people have brought up the issue of what to do with open raid loot when you will no longer use it.  My perspective on this is to do one of two things with it:<br><br>1) Pass it on to a guildy, with the condition that they treat it as open raid loot as well.<br>2) Bring it to another open raid and random it off.  Possibly use it as incentive to get people to help you on a raid.<br><br><br>Thats all for now,<br>Findra<br><br>Edit: Got booted to the Soapbox from General.  Didn't think it was that controversial.  &lt;shrug&gt;<br><br>(Syll edit: lol, the dancing post.  I'll just put it back in general.  It's not a scheduled event, so events seems off)<br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------<br>Edit 7/19/02 Midnight<br><br>Thank you all for your input.  I have decided against putting up a poll, partly because I'm lazy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>I spoke with Ericco briefly online earlier tonight.  Unfortuneately, I was in the middle of a Coldain Ring quest and he didn't have much time (sorry bud).  He has delivered 2K plat to me that he said was the proceeds from the guantlets (if he actually got 2K for them all I have to say is &quot;WOW&quot;).  I will be using this to fund future raids that I throw (roughly 3 raids worth of peridot).  Ericco is no longer banned from my raids, and I will allow him to participate fully (including rolling for loot).  As was posted several times, he has apologized and I see no reason to believe this was anything other than a big misunderstanding.<br><br>I had intended this thread to spark a discussion for future raids, and I think it has to some extent.  As someone pointed out, the Gauntlets are not 'uber' loot, but are still nice.  I kinda wanted us all to start thinking about how we (the open raid community) would react if we saw someone selling off a Cloak of Flames, or worse yet a Red Dragon Scale.<br><br>It's late, and I can't think of anything else constructive to say.<br><br>Findra <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=findra>Findra</A> at: 7/19/02 12:13:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5